<br>
Oh and 1 more thing, with all my armor on i have an AC of around 760, comparing this to some other classes that are my lvl with a higher agility such as rangers, they nearly match my AC. Why is this?<br>
<br>
Bah, ill ask 1 more. Do you think trading off hp for ac is a sensible sacrifice? e.g. upgrading a crusty set to higher ac armour, i mean you lose so much hp.<br>
<br>
Thanks for your patience.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uwubaogoldenarmz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wubao Goldenarmz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 150<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/14/02 7:45:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3895.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   you answered one question yourself ...</span><hr size=1> You ask ... &quot;Why is this?&quot;<br>
<br>
Then you ask another question that actually answers that question ... &quot;Do you think trading off hp for ac is a sensible sacrifice? e.g. upgrading a crusty set to higher ac armour, i mean you lose so much hp.&quot;<br>
<br>
Crustacean Shell armour has low AC (well, in relation to other options like Crafted and Soldier's). The people you're comparing your AC to are probably wearing better AC items than Crustacean Shell armour is all.<br>
<br>
To answer your question about wether or not sacrificing your insane STA boosted HPs from Crustacean for more AC is worth it ... that's up to you. <br>
<br>
I'd say YES. I was wearing a full suit of crafted around the time I got a chance to switch into some better HP giving crusty pieces. A few days later, I got some great deals on dragonhide armor pieces (legs, pants, sleeves and boots) and upgraded them instantly.<br>
<br>
So I wore Crustacean Shell armour for about 2 days. Heh.<br>
<br>
I'd say keep pushing for good AC until you're at least getting past 1k, and THEN start thinking about how to maximize HPs while still keeping at making your AC higher until you hit whatever AC cap you think you ought to be at.<br>
<br>
-Wu<br>
aka<br>
-Snoggy <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/udayveed.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dayveed</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/14/02 10:27:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3895.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: you answered one question yourself ...</span><hr size=1> Crusty = The Suke<br>
