<br>
 <p><A Href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=372764"> Dayveed Goliawth</A> 56th Myrmidon, Jedi Master<BR><A href="www.honor-knights.org">Honor Knights</A> E'Ci Server<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ushrimpi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shrimpi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/14/02 11:18:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3895.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: you answered one question yourself ...</span><hr size=1> The only Crusty pieces that are really worthwhile in my opinion are the bracers and the legs.<br>
Get a crafted breastplate, or a treeweave - both should be dirt cheap.<br>
<br>
<A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=107289">Shrimpi Shortshanks</A><br>
Myrmi´Gnome <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ubinnamar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Binnamar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 103<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/15/02 12:14:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3895.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: you answered one question yourself ...</span><hr size=1> This armor can also take you into your 50ies. So you don't need to fret about upgrading for a little while yet. But if you can, go ahead. <p>Binnamar- 51 dwarven warrior<BR>
Kakash- 5 Vah Shir Beastlord<BR>
Tarrew Marr<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uealsurhelevorn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ealsur Helevorn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/15/02 2:18:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3895.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: you answered one question yourself ...</span><hr size=1> Well, I was using crusty arms (and still do legs), and like you, didnt want to lose my STA, so I lurked for some arms with similar stats but higher AC, Crystal Chitin Armplates 18AC 5str 5sta 10hp was a good upgrade. Plus Im saving for a golden idol of Mith Marr 9ac 10sta and hp, so it kinda fixed the crusty STA problem. CC arms go for around 2k, its not a lot, and its kinda worth the effort of saving, besides, think that when you replace a crusty piece, you gain DEX <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
I never really used a full set of crusty, so I cant tell what set might be a good replacement. <p><div align="center"> 
<img src="http://www.strike9.com/file.aspx/path=/Ealsur/fullsize/Ealsur.jpg"><br>
<b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=251429" target="_blank">Elven Berserk of 53 Dances</a></b><br>
<em>"The Power of Metal flowing in your veins... at the Speed of Light!"</em><br>
</div>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uoulurok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Oulurok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/15/02 9:37:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3895.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: you answered one question yourself ...</span><hr size=1> I been using a full set of crusty since mid teens.  I haven't really noticed that my AC is so low I can't tank yet.  I think the hps make up for it.  My AC hasn't gone up since 45 from skill ups so it's been the same for a few levels now also.  I was tanking in Skyfire with a 54 cleric, 54 mage, and 52 Ranger and didn't here the cleric complaining.  Did need to med break after 4 or 5 fights in a row though. <p><a href= http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=144690 target=blank><center><font size=3 face=papyrus color=yellow>Oulurok</center></font></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ubauefk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>bauefk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 52<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/16/02 11:31:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3895.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: you answered one question yourself ...</span><hr size=1> I wouldnt hunt in SS. I DID and now Im paying the price. Ive been killing Giants for weeks and weeks and weeks ...<br>
SS quest armor from HoT is very nice stuff. Ive got 2 bits of  the quest parts gathering dust in my backpacks now cause I trashed my faction hunting in SS . If your not planning to jumping into a guild thats allready on giant faction and hunting in NToV save your dwarf and dragon faction. <br>
<br>
Crusty should take you right up to the level that you can get champs from Kael. <br>
<br>
...Just the thoughts of a troll.....<br>
-Big B <p><a href=  "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=20746" Target=blank My stuffs</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/umistwolfeq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MistwolfEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 88<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/16/02 11:56:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3895.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: you answered one question yourself ...</span><hr size=1> Depends on how much mola you have access to.  The more cash mean better stuff, thats all.  Some upgrades I went to for the buck is cobalt.  I went from crusty to cobalt pieces (takes a while, just do it one at at time) and Ive seen a big jump in my tanking ability.  Things hit me less and less as I get more and more cobalt.<br>
<br>
Dunno about your server, but the boots, gloves, and arms are pretty common.  With a lot of them for sale, the price drops to reasonable figures.  For the other parts, its tough to upgrade so I stuck to crusty till I had enough to move up. <br>
<br>
Depends on your situation.  If you can get more cash by yourself then save up and buy pieces.  If you owe your hide to a guild, then get some nice raid pieces.  But at mid 30's, I would think buying would be better.  Crusty lasted me well into my 50's till I started working more on gear then my lvl.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showPrevMessage?topicID=3895.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showNextMessage?topicID=3895.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3895.topic&index=8><img src=http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/swaddreply.GIF border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.emailToFriend?topicID=3895.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.threadControl?topicID=3895.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3895.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3895.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub14.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr>